<recipe>
<title>
Oatmeal Cookie Pancakes
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 c . old fashioned oat
1 c . all-purpose flour (you can also substitute 1/2 cup of whole wheat flour for half of the all-purpose flour)
1/2 c . brown sugar , packed
2 tsp . baking powder
1/2 tsp . baking soda
1 tsp . ground cinnamon
1/2 tsp . ground nutmeg
3/4 c . fat-free Greek yogurt
3/4 c . low-fat milk
2 large eggs
1 tsp . vanilla extract
2 really ripe bananas , mashed up
1/4 c . (4 T.) butter, melted, divided
1/2 c . chopped pecans or walnuts (optional)
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Mix dry ingredients, the first 6, in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the wet ingredients, the next 4.
Whisk the wet ingredients into the dry until just combined, then fold in the mashed up bananas.
Stir in 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Add chopped nuts, if using.
Heat a griddle over medium heat and brush with additional melted butter.
Cook pancakes about 1/3 cup at a time, until bubbles form on the top, then turn.
Pancakes will cook in about 2 minutes on each side.
</instructions>
</recipe>
